# Project Architecture — Feature-Sliced Design

## Directory Structure

```
src/
  app/              # Expo Router routes (thin re-exports only)
  application/      # App shell: layouts, providers, app-level libs
  entities/         # Domain slices: family, period, purchase, profile, auth, subscription
  screens/          # Full-page screens (one per route)
  widgets/          # Reusable multi-component UI blocks
  shared/           # Cross-cutting: config, lib, ui, storage
```

## Path Aliases (tsconfig)

`@app/*`, `@screens/*`, `@widgets/*`, `@entities/*`, `@shared/*`, `@features/*`, `@assets/*`

## Entity Structure

Each entity follows `libs/` + `model/` + `index.ts`:

```
entities/family/
  libs/getFamily.ts, getMembers.ts, createFamily.ts, updateFamily.ts, ...
  model/types.ts, family-store.ts
  index.ts          # Barrel — every public export goes here
```

- `libs/` — Supabase queries and mutations (one function per file)
- `model/types.ts` — TypeScript types for the domain object
- `model/*-store.ts` — Zustand store (in-memory, not persisted)
- `index.ts` — Re-exports everything. Consumers import from `@entities/family`, never deep paths.

## Screen Structure

```
screens/dashboard/
  ui/DashboardScreen.tsx
  index.ts           # export { default } from './ui/DashboardScreen'
```

## Route Files (src/app/)

Route files are thin re-exports. No logic, no UI:

```tsx
// src/app/(app)/(tabs)/history.tsx
export { default } from '@screens/history';
```

## Shared Layer

- `shared/ui/` — Primitive components: Button, Card, Input, ScreenContent
- `shared/lib/` — Pure utilities: env, format, theme, period math, settlement calc
- `shared/config/` — Supabase client, RevenueCat config
- `shared/storage/` — AsyncStorage adapters (e.g. supabase-storage)

## Key Rules

- Zustand stores are in-memory only — never assume data survives restart
- The `AppGateProvider` is the source of truth for auth state, profile, and family on app start
- Dashboard and other screens should read `family` from `useAppGateContext()`, not from the Zustand store
- Supabase session persists via AsyncStorage (supabaseStorage adapter)
- `fiftyfifty:welcomed` and `fiftyfifty:pending_invite` are AsyncStorage keys for onboarding state (`@shared/lib/storage/appStorageKeys`); legacy `haven:*` keys are migrated once on read
